== Variation of color ==
=== Dark Byzantine blue === Dark Byzantine blue is the dark variation of Byzantine blue, best described as the color of Byzantine [[night sky]], close to nuances of dark blue grey, [[blue-grey|blue grey]], [[Prussian blue|Prussian]] and [[Navy blue]], well attested on frescoes and [[mosaics]].<ref name="art-paints">{{cite web|url=http://www.art-paints.com/Paints/Oil/Mussini-Resin/Byzantine-Blue/Byzantine-Blue.html|title=Byzantine Blue Schmincke Oil Paints - 495 - Byzantine Blue Paint, Byzantine Blue Color, Mussini Resin Schmincke Paint, 2A2F4D|website=Art-Paints.com|accessdate=2017-09-19}}</ref> {{infobox color|textcolor=black| title=Dark Byzantine blue| hex=2A2F4D| r=42|g= 47|b= 77| c= 45|m= 39|y= 0|k= 70| h=231|s= 45|v= 30
