{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2016}} {{Use British English|date=May 2016}} {{Infobox television | show_name = X-Rated Ambition: The Traci Lords Story | image = | image_size = | image_alt = | caption = | genre = | creator = | based_on = | writer = | screenplay = | story = | director = Simon Kerslake | starring = | narrated = Jo Unwin | music = James Dorman | country = United Kingdom | language = English | producer = {{Plainlist| * [[World of Wonder (production company)|Fenton Bailey]] (exec.) * [[World of Wonder (production company)|Randy Barbato]] (exec.) * Helen Booth * Simon Kerslake * Adam Perry (exec.) }} | editor = Mark Henson | runtime = 50 minutes | company = {{Plainlist| * [[Channel 5 (UK)|Channel 5]] * [[World of Wonder (production company)|World of Wonder]] }} | distributor = Channel 5 | first_aired = 2003 }}
'''''X-Rated Ambition: The Traci Lords Story''''' is a 2003 British [[documentary film]] directed by Simon Kerslake. It follows American actress [[Traci Lords]]' career in the [[Pornography|adult film industry]] when she, at the age of only 15, became one of the biggest pornstars. The documentary features interviews with many of her co-workers from that time including porn agent [[Jim South]], photographer [[Suze Randall]] and pornstars [[Tom Byron]], [[Ginger Lynn]], [[Peter North (actor)|Peter North]], [[Ron Jeremy]], [[Amber Lynn]] and [[Nina Hartley]].
==Plot== In 1984, a young girl named Kristie Elizabeth Nussman walked into the office of the porn agent Jim South searching for a job. She became known as Traci Lords, one of the most sought-after pornstars of the 1980s. However, nobody knew that Nussman was actually Nora Kuzma, a fifteen-year-old runaway who by the time she was eighteen had already appeared in dozens of X-rated films.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://worldofwonder.net/productions/x-rated-ambition-traci-lords/|title=Traci Lords: X-Rated Ambition|date=12 April 2004|website=[[World of Wonder (production company)|World of Wonder]]|access-date=12 August 2015}}</ref>
